Markus,

> After starting r3.showdspf from within Grass with no command-line
> arguments you should get the following prompt:> "Name of existing color
> table".
> 
> After getting this prompt, enter the name of a file located in the current
> working directory that is created manually.  That file should have lines
> similar to the ones shown below:
> 
> .000010:0:0:255
> 0.183342:0:255:255
> 0.366673:0:255:0
> 0.550005:255:255:0
> 0.733337:255:0:0
> 0.916668:55:0:255
> 1.100000:55:55:255
> 
> Each lines have 4 fields separated by colons. 
> Field 1 contains a threshold value
> Field 2 contains a red color component where 0 <= red <= 255
> Field 3 contains a green color component where 0 <= green <= 255
> Field 4 contains a blue color component where 0 <= blue <= 255
> 
> I hope that this helps.
> 
Steve


